# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for changes to specific paths.
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Currently a single-maintainer repo; this file ensures every PR is
# routed for review. Add team members above @hlsitechio as the project
# grows to require domain-specific review.

# Default owner for everything
*                                            @hlsitechio

# Skill content — every PR touching a SKILL.md or its references
# needs a maintainer review because the content drives real audits.
*/SKILL.md                                   @hlsitechio
**/references/*.md                           @hlsitechio
**/_shared/*.md                              @hlsitechio

# Inventory — version drift surface; CVE / source claims must be
# verified before merge.
/.github/tech-inventory.yml                  @hlsitechio

# CI workflows + repo-level security policy — high blast radius.
/.github/workflows/                          @hlsitechio
/.github/CODEOWNERS                          @hlsitechio
/SECURITY.md                                 @hlsitechio
/.github/SECURITY.md                         @hlsitechio

# Packaging + bulk-upload scripts — touch them carefully.
**/scripts/                                  @hlsitechio
/scripts/                                    @hlsitechio
